This directory contains every material needed to create the database
required by the xmppmaster module to store its informations.

As the PULSE2 evolve, so does the xmppmaster database. This directory contains the
base schema (schema-001.sql) and subsequents evolutions (schema-xxx.sql).

To obtain a state-of-the-art xmppmaster database, just run the install script.


mysql> source /usr/share/doc/mmc/contrib/xmppmaster/sql/schema-001.sql

mysql> SHOW GRANTS FOR 'mmc'@'localhost';
+------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Grants for mmc@localhost                                                                                   |
+------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| GRANT USAGE ON *.* TO 'mmc'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY PASSWORD '*5987sqdsqfdqfqfqqfqfqfqfsqfc<cd<<qFC' |
| GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON `update`.* TO 'mmc'@'localhost'                                                    |
| GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON `report`.* TO 'mmc'@'localhost'                                                    |
| GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON `backuppc`.* TO 'mmc'@'localhost'                                                  |
| GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON `pulse2`.* TO 'mmc'@'localhost'                                                    |
| GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON `msc`.* TO 'mmc'@'localhost'                                                       |
| GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON `inventory`.* TO 'mmc'@'localhost'                                                 |
| GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON `imaging`.* TO 'mmc'@'localhost'                                                   |
| GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON `dyngroup`.* TO 'mmc'@'localhost'                                                  |
+------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+

verify 
GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON `xmppmaster`.*  TO 'mmc'@'localhost' 

else
mysql> GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON `xmppmaster`.*  TO 'mmc'@'localhost' ;

